<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
     HISTORY
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="rct-history" class="history">
  <div class="history__inner">

    <!-- Left: title + first paragraph -->
    <div class="history__left">
      <h2 class="history__title fade">History</h2>
      <p class="fade d1">In 1996, Roberto Coin introduced Appassionata, the first collection to feature a hidden ruby, a symbol of protection, passion and prosperity. This signature detail became the heart of the Maison.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Center: ring illustration with multiply blend -->
    <div class="history__center fade">
      <img src="{{ 'figma-images/History-Ring drawing.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Roberto Coin ring illustration">
    </div>

    <!-- Right: second paragraph -->
    <div class="history__right">
      <p class="fade d1">Guided by Roberto Coin's creative vision and brought to life by master Italian artisans, the brand quickly gained international recognition. In 2000, he became a founding member of the World Diamond Council, supporting the Kimberley Process. Today, the Maison is present in over 60 countries worldwide, and the ruby remains its enduring symbol.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
     THE CREATOR
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="rct-creator" class="creator">
  <div class="creator__inner">
    <div class="creator__image">
      <img src="{{ 'figma-images/creator-portrait.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="Roberto Coin">
    </div>
    <div class="creator__text">
      <h2 class="creator__title fade">The Creator</h2>
      <div class="creator__body">
        <p class="fade d1">Roberto Coin’s journey did not begin in jewelry. After a successful career in luxury hospitality across Europe, he returned to Italy and immersed himself in the goldsmith tradition of Vicenza. In 1984, he began designing under his own name, marking the start of a new creative chapter.</p>
        <p class="fade d2">At 33, he returned to Italy and immersed himself in the goldsmith tradition of Vicenza, the historic heart of Italian jewelry. In 1984, he began designing under his own name, transforming experience into creativity and vision into craftsmanship. That decision marked the true beginning of the Maison.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <img class="creator__vicenza" src="{{ 'figma-images/Vicenza_drawing_image.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Vicenza drawing">
</section>

<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
     THE RUBY
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section id="rct-ruby" class="ruby-section">
  <div class="ruby-section__bg"></div>
  <div class="ruby-section__overlay"></div>
  <div class="ruby-section__inner">
    <div class="ruby-section__content">
      <h2 class="ruby-section__title fade">The Ruby</h2>
      <div class="ruby-section__body">
        <p class="fade d1">Roberto Coin chose the ruby as the hidden signature of his creations.</p>

        <p class="fade d2">Inspired by ancient cultures, where the ruby symbolized protection, vitality and passion, he transformed it into a discreet talisman worn close to the skin.</p>

        <p class="fade">Set inside every jewel, the ruby is not meant to be seen but to be felt. A quiet symbol of strength, courage and enduring beauty that connects each creation to its wearer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="ruby-section__gem fade d1">
      <img src="{{ 'figma-images/ruby-gem.png' | asset_url }}" alt="The Hidden Ruby">
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

